      "weather": "Overcast",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RITZA TIANA (1) had the drop on the lead before drawing clear to score (29.38) at this track in Grade 5 over 520m. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. GEMMA KEEPING (7) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at Q Parklands over 520m behind Neame (30.61) in a Grade 4/5. Placed at her previous run. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Shapes as one to consider. SWIFT WIND (6) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.75 lengths at Maitland in a handy 25.21 beating Heatherly Lomar. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Has definite claims. CONDO BANDIT (4) is in the mix following a brief let-up.",
